xNzgzNTA2MDQ2fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Ping Onganankun"},"description":"South Korea's capital and primary entry point for most visitors, serving as the transport hub to reach Gangwon's attractions. While technically in a different province, it's essential for accessing trains and buses to Gangwon destinations."},{"rank":2,"name":"Jeju Island","placeId":"jeju_island","regionId":"jeju","regionName":"Jeju","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1616798249081-30877e213b16?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxKZWp1JTIwSXNsYW5kJTIwU291dGglMjBLb3JlYXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzg0MDI3MDY4fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"N Riazi"},"description":"A volcanic island and premier vacation destination known for its natural beauty, beaches, and unique landscape including Hallasan mountain. It attracts millions annually for relaxation, outdoor activities, and its distinct cultural heritage."},{"rank":3,"name":"Busan","placeId":"busan","regionId":"gyeongnam","regionName":"South Gyeongsang","image":null,"description":"South Korea's second-largest city and primary port, Busan is a vibrant coastal metropolis famous for its beaches, seafood markets, and modern skyline. Essential stops include Gamcheon Culture Village, Jagalchi Fish Market, and Haeundae Beach."},{"rank":4,"name":"Gyeongbokgung Palace","placeId":"gyeongbokgung_palace","regionId":"seoul","regionName":"Seoul","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1638964663550-e2123ac8900b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxHeWVvbmdib2tndW5nJTIwUGFsYWNlJTIwU2VvdWx8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzUwNTkzM3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Daniel Bernard"},"description":"The largest and most iconic of Seoul's five grand palaces, built in 1395 during the Joseon Dynasty. It showcases traditional Korean architecture, royal guards in ceremonial uniforms, and offers a deep dive into Korean royal history."},{"rank":5,"name":"Namsan Tower (Seoul Tower)","placeId":"namsan_tower","regionId":"seoul","regionName":"Seoul","image":null,"description":"An iconic 237-meter observation tower offering panoramic views of Seoul's skyline from multiple levels. Tourists visit for the spectacular vistas, dining options, and the tower's status as a symbol of Seoul."},{"rank":6,"name":"Incheon","placeId":"incheon_city","regionId":"incheon","regionName":"Incheon","image":null,"description":"South Korea's third-largest city and a major international hub, home to Incheon International Airport and the gateway to Korea. The city blends modern development with historical significance, featuring diverse neighborhoods and cultural attractions."},{"rank":7,"name":"Myeongdong","placeId":"myeongdong","regionId":"seoul","regionName":"Seoul","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1760020954071-13a2c86076ff?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNeWVvbmdkb25nJTIwU2VvdWwlMjBzaG9wcGluZyUyMHN0cmVldHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNTA1OTM1fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Jin-Woo Lee"},"description":"Seoul's premier shopping and entertainment district packed with international brands, street food vendors, and bustling crowds day and night. It's the heart of Korean pop culture and fashion where locals and tourists converge."},{"rank":8,"name":"Nami Island","placeId":"nami_island","regionId":"gyeonggi","regionName":"Gyeonggi","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1553710584-5e5f462994bc?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxOYW1pJTIwSXNsYW5kJTIwYXV0dW1ufGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM1MDYwMjV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Joshua Delica"},"description":"A scenic crescent-shaped island in the Han River near Seoul famous for its tree-lined paths, autumn foliage, and spring blossoms. It gained international fame from the Korean drama Winter Sonata and offers peaceful walks, cycling, and river views."},{"rank":9,"name":"Gwangju","placeId":"gwangju_city","regionId":"jeonnam","regionName":"South Jeolla","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1696250753322-94a5adbca94d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxHd2FuZ2p1JTIwY2l0eSUyMHNreWxpbmUlMjBLb3JlYXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNTEyMjMwfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"bluegold H"},"description":"South Korea's fifth-largest city and cultural hub, known for its art museums, May 18 Democratic Uprising history, and vibrant food scene. The city is home to the Gwangju Biennale, Asia's leading contemporary art festival, and offers excellent museums and galleries."},{"rank":10,"name":"Bulguksa Temple","placeId":"bulguksa_temple","regionId":"gyeongbuk","regionName":"North Gyeongsang","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1596018382916-56d2e341d784?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCdWxndWtzYSUyMFRlbXBsZSUyMHN0b25lJTIwcGFnb2Rhc3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNTEyMzEyfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Srusti Valakamadinni"},"description":"One of Korea's most important Buddhist temples, Bulguksa is a masterpiece of Silla architecture built in 751 AD, featuring beautiful stone pagodas, bridges, and intricate wooden structures set against forested mountains. It's a UNESCO World Heritage site and essential to any visit to North Gyeongsang."}]}